data.24: Contributory Value of Repairs and Improvements
data.A1: Acids - A value, normally shown as a percent of the total, showing the content of all acidic structures contained in a solution of a known product
data.A2: Adsorption - A value defining the adhesion in an extremely thin layer of molecules (as of gases, solutes, or liquids) to the surfaces of solid bodies or liquids with which they are in contact
data.A3: Aging Time - The time taken, once a product has been initially manufactured, to come to a desired quality through undisturbed rest or curing; also, the time taken to bring to a desired use or maturity
data.A4: Aromatics - A value, normally shown as a percent of the total, showing the content of all molecules in a product containing at least one benzene ring
data.A5: Average Differential Pressure - Average difference between the upstream and downstream pressure through an orifice plate; expressed in inches of water
data.A6: Average Static Pressure - Pressure of the flowing gas stream; expressed in pounds per square inch
data.A7: Flame Projection Distance - The distance that a flame would project from an aerosol can containing the subject material if ignited
data.A9: Exposure - A measure of the quantity of a specified form of energy or mass coming into contact with another specified object or space
data.AAP: AC-apparent Power - Power measurement of a material subject to a magnetic induction
data.ABO: Absorbance - The negative base 10 logarithm of the ratio of the radiant power transmitted by a sample to the radiant power incident upon the sample
data.ABR: Abrasion - The qualitative ability of a surface to wear, grind, and rub away or to be worn away
data.ABS: Absorbency - The rate at which a specimen takes up liquids or the amount of liquid required to saturate the specimen
data.ACN: Acid Number - The quantity of base required to titrate acidic constituents present
data.ADH: Adhesion - The molecular attraction between two or more bodies in contact
data.AGE: Inventory Age - The age of inventory from the date or time of production to the present date or time
data.AJ: Aim Gage - Physical dimension a producer is to "aim" toward producing or supplying
data.AK: Volatile Organic Compounds (VOCs) - Organic compounds whose existence is calculable or detectable by methods specified by the U.S. Environmental Protection Agency
data.ALK: Alkalinity - The quantitative capacity of aqueous media to react with hydrogen ions
data.ALN: Alkalinity Number - The quantity of acid required to titrate basic constituents present
data.ALP: Alpha-Cellulose - The average molecular chain length of pure long-chain cellulose in pulp
data.AMI: Amines - Content of basic compounds derived from ammonia by replacement of hydrogen by one or more univalent hydrocarbon radicals or other non-acidic organic radicals
data.AMW: Average Molecular Weight - The average of the sums of the weights of molecules' constituent atoms in an object which contains more than one type of molecule
data.AOX: Antioxidant - A substance that increases a product's oxidation resistance
data.API: API Gravity - A special hydrometer scale recommended for exclusive use in the U.S. Petroleum Industry for liquids lighter than water
data.APP: Appearance - The visible impression of an item
data.ASH: Ash - The inorganic component of product
data.ASY: Assay - The quantitative determination of the amount of the major or active component of an item
data.B1: Base Number - A number that identifies the ability of a compound to react with an acid to either take up a proton from the acid or to give up unshared electrons to an acid to form a salt
data.B5: Octanol/Water Partition Coefficient - A scientific measure of the relative solubility of a material in octonol versus its solubility in water
data.BDP: Perforation Bottom Depth - The deepest depth below surface level for perforations in the well casing
data.BHF: Bottomhole Pressure - Flowing - Fluid pressure at the deepest depth in the well bore while production is flowing from the well; measured during well testing and completion operations
data.BHS: Bottomhole Pressure - Shutin - Fluid pressure at the deepest depth in the well bore with the well annulus closed; measured during well testing and completion operations
data.BIC: Bark in Chips - The ratio of tree bark to wood chips; indicates the level of one type of contamination in production of wood pulp
data.BJ: Burst Index - The burst pressure of a paper or pulp sheet expressed per unit basis weight
data.BN: Bend - The ability of the product to undergo bending operation in forming
data.BND: Amount Bound in Material - Amount that cannot be removed by volatilization, solvent extraction, or melting
data.BOR: Boiling Range - The temperatures normally used or required to bring a substance to boil at different barometric pressures
data.BRS: Breaking Strength - The greatest longitudinal stress a substance can bear without tearing apart
data.C1: Carbonyl - The measurement of the bivalent carbon-oxygen radical occurring in aldehydes, ketones, carboxylic acids, esters, acid halides, and amides; also, the measurement of the compound carbonyl radical with a metal
data.C2: Catalyst - The measurement of any number of substances used in the production of a final product or retained in the final product that initiates a chemical reaction and enable the product to proceed under milder conditions than otherwise possible
data.C3: Maximum Contraction - A result from a process that measures the total contraction of a sample
data.CAU: Caustic Reaction Severity - The severity of chemical reaction due to caustic present as the primary reactant
data.CGR: Color Grayness RD - Lightness or darkness of cotton
data.CHA: Chemical Addition Rate - The quantity of chemical expressed by weight or volume added to manufacturing or testing process per unit of time
data.CHG: Rate of Change - The increase or decrease in polarity and amount of a change per unit of time
data.CHL: Chlorides - Amount of chlorides in the water or brine produced from a well
data.CIV: Cuene Intrinsic Viscosity - The average molecular weight of cellulose molecules in product
data.CLA: Clarity - The clearness or transparency of an item
data.CLN: Cleanliness - The impurities remaining in and/or on the product
data.COH: Coercive Force - Magnetizing force at which magnetic induction is zero
data.COL: Color - The aspect of appearance dependent upon the wavelength of incident, reflected or transmitted, and observed light
data.CON: Concentration - The relative amount of a component of a sample of product containing multiple components
data.COR: Corrosiveness - The ability to destroy gradually by chemical reaction
data.COT: Content - The amount of specified material contained
data.CPF: Casing Pressure - Flowing - Fluid pressure within the casing, or outermost tubing used to isolate the well from the surrounding geology, while production is flowing from the well; measured during well testing and completion operations
data.CPS: Casing Pressure - Shutin - Fluid pressure within the casing, or outermost tubing used to isolate the well from the surrounding geology, with the well annulus closed; measured during well testing and completion operations
data.CRN: Crown - Increase in the thickness or height of a rolled product at the center compared to the thickness at the edge
data.CSC: Choke Size - Casing - The diameter of the orifice in the casing through which liquids flow
data.CST: Choke Size - Tubing - The diameter of the orifice in the tubing through which liquids flow
data.CTG: Coating - Product applied to the top of a substrate or base
data.CUT: Cure Time - The time required to prepare a product by chemical or physical processing for storage or use
data.CY: Contamination - The yellowness of cotton; correlates with the spotted and light spotted part of the classer grade; higher values represent more yellowness
data.D1: Maximum Dilatation - A result from a process that measures the total expansion of a sample
data.D2: Dispersing Agent - The measurement of the amount of substance that promotes the formation and stabilization of a dispersion of one substance in another
data.D3: Drying Agent - The measurement of the amount of substance in a product that is used to extract liquid from either the manufacture or use of a product
data.D4: Dry Point - A temperature measurement used in a distillation process to identify the temperature at which a product becomes dry
data.DAT: Datum Depth - Depth below ground surface at which a measurement is taken within a well
data.DCT: Dirt Count - The amount of visible contamination
data.DEM: De Minimis Level - A measurable level of significance below which a requirement does not apply
data.DIR: Distillation Range - The temperature range in which a defined amount of material boils under specified conditions
data.DIS: Dispersion - The ease with which one substance mixes with another
data.DME: Dichloromethane Extract - The volatile components of pulp products
data.DPM: Degree of Polymerization - The average number of monomer units per polymer molecule in product
data.DR: Delta R - Planar variation of r value which is defined by the following equation: (r0 - 2r45 + r90)/2
data.DRY: Dryness - A product specification in pulp, paper, and chemicals
data.DWP: Dew Point - The temperature at which a vapor begins to condense
data.E1: End - Identifies a value measured at the end of a testing process or range of test results
data.EL: Elasticity - The springiness or rebound of a deformed material
data.ELI: Immediately Dangerous to Life and Health - A measurable level beyond which the most stringent safety measures, such as evacuation, must be taken
data.ELO: Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) Permissible Exposure Limit
data.ELP: Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) Permissible Exposure Limit Ceiling
data.ELS: American Conference of Government Industrial Hygienists (ACGIH) Threshold Limit Value: Short-Term Exposure
data.ELT: American Conference of Governmental Industrial Hygienists (ACGIH) Threshold Limit Value: Time Weighted Average
data.ELW: American Industrial Hygienists Association (AIHA) Work Environment Exposure Level (WEEL)
data.ELX: American Industrial Hygienists Association (AIHA) Work Environment Exposure Level (WEEL): Time Weighted Average
data.EVL: Evaporation Loss - The amount of material lost under specified conditions
data.EXH: Exhaust Benzene Emissions - Benzene emissions from the exhaust system
data.EXT: Extractables - Material removed by solvent extraction
data.F1: Fire Point - The measurement of the temperature at which combustion initially begins for any number of substances
data.FBP: Acetate Break Point - The chemical reactivity of cellulose in the acetylation process
data.FIL: Filter Number - The filterability of a solution expressed in units combining the porosity of the filter medium and the time required for a standard volume of solution to pass through the filter at specific pressures
data.FIN: Fineness - Mean fiber width in micrograms per inch
data.FIT: Filterability - The ability of a substance to pass through a given medium under specified conditions
data.FJ: Face Width - The width of the oscillate wound material
data.FK: Fluid Consistency - Descriptor of a fluid expressed as the ratio, by weight, of total suspended solids to liquid
data.FLD: Fluid Point - The point at which the fused mass has spread out in a nearly flat layer with a maximum height of 1/16 in. (1.6 mm)
data.FLN: Fiber Length - Instrument method of measuring length in hundredths of an inch
data.FLP: Fluid Level Above Pump - The depth of well liquids above the location of a subsurface pump unit
data.FNL: Fines Retained on Screen - Amount of particles in a material that is larger than a defined unit
data.FNS: Fines - The amount of particles in a material that are smaller than a defined limit
data.FOA: Foam - The dispersion of gas in a liquid or solid
data.FOI: Fouling Index - The result of a procedure which represents the accumulation of deposits of ash on superheater, boiler and economizer tubes
data.FOR: Foreign Matter - The visible contamination in a material
data.FPV: Acetate Plugging Value - The weight of a liquid that passes through a given area of filter at a constant filtration pressure before the filter becomes completely blocked or plugged; denotes the filtration quality of viscose or solutions of cellulose acetate
data.FSI: Free Swelling Index - The result of a procedure regarding the caking properties of coal when burned as fuel
data.G2: Grain Size - The internal grain morphology of a sample
data.GGR: Gas Gravity - The density of the produced gas relative to the density of air at standard temperature and pressure
data.GI: Grit, Brushed - The percentage of a sample of TiO2 (water dispersed) which remains on a 325 mesh screen after washing and brushing the screen and surface to break apart soft agglomerates
data.GIR: Gas Injection Test Rate - Volume of gas injected into the well bore during a 24-hour test period
data.GJ: Grit, Unbrushed - The percentage of a sample of TiO2 (water dispersed) which remains on a 325 mesh screen after washing the screen surface
data.GK: Tinting Strength - A measure of the hiding power of a titanium dioxide sample obtained by comparing the green (Y) reflectance of a tinted waterbased formula against that of a standard
data.GM: Emulsion Gloss - The 60-degree gloss of a pigment sample in a waterbased paint formula
data.GO: Particle End Point - The reading on a Hegman gauge, below the fineness line, at which the population of scattered particles stops
data.GOR: Gas-to-Oil Ratio - A measure of the gas produced from a hydrocarbon well relative to the oil produced
data.GQ: Scattered Particles - The number of scattered particles (visible defects) in a drawdown on a Hegman gauge between the fineness line and the particle end point
data.GRA: Gas Test Rate - Volume of gas produced from a well during a 24-hour test period
data.GRI: Graininess - The crystallinity of a substance
data.GS: Carbon Black Undertone - The blue/amber ratio (Z/X) of the reflectance of a paste made of titanium dioxide and carbon black; a measure of the TiO2 particle size
data.GT: Glass Transition Temperature - Temperature at which an amorphous material changes from a brittle to a plastic state
data.H1: Heavies - A relative term that is used to identify the weight percent of all molecules beyond the peak identified as the molecule being tested for in a gas chromatograph result; also, all molecules that have a boiling point higher than the molecule being tested
data.HD: High Propagation Delay Time - The time between the specified reference points on the input and output waveforms, with the output changing from the defined low level to the defined high level
data.HHW: Hemispherical Point - The point at which the cone has fused down to a hemispherical lump at which point the height is one half the width of the base as shown by the fourth cone
data.HIB: High Boilers - The components of a mixture which boil at a higher temperature than the rest of the mixture
data.HL: Heat Loss - Quantity of original thermal energy removed
data.HVM: Heavy Metals - The metals of atomic weight greater than sodium that form soaps of reaction with fatty acids
data.HWS: Softening Point - The point at which the cone has fused down to a spherical lump in which the height is equal to the width at the base
data.HYD: Hydroxyl Number - The alkalinity of oil, fat, wax or other substances
data.IA: Imperfections - Thicks - Thick places in the yarn
data.IDE: Identification - The distinguishing characteristics of a material for verification purposes
data.IE: Imperfections - Thins - Thin points in the yarn
data.IGR: Input Gas Rate - Volume of gas input during a 24-hour test period
data.IL: Imperfections - Neps - Short, broken or immature fibers in the yarn
data.IMP: Impurities - The amount of components other than the major or active components in an item
data.IN: Input Low Current - The current flowing out of input when a specified low-level voltage is applied to that input
data.IND: Initial Deformation Point - The point at which the first rounding of the apex of the cone occurs
data.INS: Insolubles - The residue remaining after dissolving an item in a solvent
data.IO: Input High Current - The current flowing out of an input when a specified high level voltage is applied to that input
data.IP: Input Leakage Current - The current flowing into an input when the maximum allowed voltage is applied to that input
data.IQ: Input Clamp Diode Voltage - The most negative voltage at an input when the specified current is forced out of that input terminal
data.IRA: Inclusion Rating - The internal nonmetallic particles in the product
data.JOM: Jominy Hardenability - The product's hardness and depth of hardening
data.L1: Lights - A relative term that is used to identify the weight percent of all molecules below the peak identified as the molecule being tested for in a gas chromatograph result; also, all molecules that have a boiling point lower than the molecule being tested
data.LC: Low Propagation Delay Time - The time between the specified reference points on the input and output waveforms, with the output changing from high level to the defined low level
data.LC5: Lethal Concentration, 50% ("LC-50") - The lowest value of concentration which will result in the death of exactly one half of a given biological test population
data.LD5: Lethal Dose, 50% ("LD-50") - The lowest value of dose which will result in the death of exactly one half of a given biological test population
data.LDH: Limited Dome Height (LDH) - Response to simulated drawing operation
data.LEF: Leaf - Percentage of leaf in fiber as determined by trash count and trash area
data.LIR: Liquid Injection Test Rate - Volume of liquids, such as oil, mud, and water, which are injected into the well during a 24-hour test period
data.LIV: Limit Intrinsic Viscosity - The percent of cellulose in a crystalline rather than amorphous form
data.LOI: Loss on Ignition - Loss (of material) that occurs when a sample is ignited
data.LOS: Loss on Drying - The amount of material lost after heating to a constant weight at a specified temperature
data.LOW: Low Boilers - The components of a mixture which boil at a lower temperature than the rest of the mixture
data.LPR: Line Pressure - Fluid pressure of the production line between the well and the separator unit or gathering line
data.LSK: Length Shrinkage - The amount of shrinkage occurring per linear yard of fabric expressed in percentage
data.LSS: Linear Sheet Swelling - The increased size of a sheet of pulp when immersed in caustic during pulping
data.LTD: Liner Top Depth - Depth below the surface of the top of a liner string; liner is a tube within the casing used to separate different strata but does not extend to the surface
data.M1: Melt Range - A range of temperatures used to identify at what point compounds start to transform from a solid to a liquid state
data.M2: Maximum Differential Pressure - The largest differential pressure reading at which this device will measure the differential pressure accurately
data.M3: Maximum Static Pressure - Largest flowing gas pressure at which this device will measure volumes accurately
data.MAT: Maturity - Swelling and compression of fiber
data.MD: Measurement Voltage - The reference voltage level on AC waveforms for determining AC performance
data.ME: Maximum Input Low Voltage - The guaranteed input low threshold
data.MEL: Melt Time - The time between the first appearance of liquid and the total disappearance of solid
data.MER: Efficient Rate-Reservoir - The maximum daily oil or gas withdrawal rate from a hydrocarbon reservoir
data.MF: Minimum Input High Voltage - The guaranteed input high voltage
data.MHI: Highest Torque - Highest torque attained during specified period of time when no plateau or maximum torque is obtained
data.MIC: Micronaire - Fiber fineness; the higher the value, the courser the fiber
data.MOI: Moisture - The amount of water in an item
data.MPR: Production Rate-Well - The maximum daily rate of at which oil or gas may be produced from a hydrocarbon well
data.MQ: MCQuaid - Austenitic grain morphology of a sample
data.MR: Module R (R Bar) - Ratio of true width strain to true thickness strain; indicates the ability of the material to resist thinning and deform in draw
data.MTD: Maximum Total Depth - Total distance along the well bore to the final bottom hole location
data.MUL: Mullen - The energy required to burst a sheet with one of several standard pluggers
data.NEU: Neutralization Number - The quantity of acid or base required to neutralize basic or acidic constituents in a substance
data.NH: Number of Items per Package Label
data.NI: Number of Splices per Package Label
data.NIL: Nil Ductility Test - The condition required to initiate brittle fracture
data.NJ: Number of Sheets per Package Label
data.NNW: Net Net Weight - The weight of an item exclusive of the weight of any shipping packaging and of any additional packaging or attachments such as cellophane wrapping or hangers
data.NON: Non-Volatile Matter - The amount of residue remaining after an analytical process
data.NOX: NOx Emissions Performance - Difference in exhaust NOx emissions attributed to a gasoline formulation as compared to the 1990 baseline gasoline
data.NV: N Value - The work hardening rate capability of material and predicts the ability to deform in stretch, plane strain, and bending
data.OC: Output Low Voltage - The maximum guaranteed low voltage at an output terminal sinking the specified load-current output low current
data.OCG: Oil/Condensate Gravity - Production fluid density relative to the density of water
data.OCR: Oil/Condensate Test Rate - Volume of oil and natural gas condensate produced during a 24-hour test period
data.ODR: Odor - The quality of a substance that stimulates the olfactory organ
data.OE: Output Low Current - The current flowing into an output which is in the low state
data.OF: Output High Voltage - The minimum guaranteed high voltage at an output terminal for the specified output current 'output high current' and at the minimum VCC value
data.OG: Output High Current - The leakage current flowing into a turned-off, open-collector output with a specified high output voltage applied
data.OI: Output Off Current Low - The current flowing out of a disabled three-state output with a specified low output voltage applied
data.OIL: Oil - Liquid, slippery, viscous, relatively nonvolatile chemical
data.OJ: Output Off Current High - The current flowing into a disabled three-state output with a specified high output voltage applied
data.OK: Output Short-Circuit Current - The current flowing out of an output which is in the high state when that output is short circuit to ground
data.OL: Output Disable Time from Low Level of a 3-State Output - The delay time between the specified reference points on the input and output voltage waveforms with the three-state output changing from the low level to a high impedance 'off' state
data.ON: Output Disable Time from High Level of a 3-State Output - The delay time between the specified reference points on the input and output voltage waveforms with three-state output changing from the high level to a high impedance 'off' state
data.OO: Output Enable Time from Low Level of a 3-State Output - The delay time between the specified reference points on the input and output voltage waveforms with the three-state output changing from the high impedance 'off' state to the low level
data.OQ: Output Enable Time from High Level of a 3-State Output - The delay time between the specified reference points on the input and output voltage waveforms with the three-state output changing from high impedance 'off' state to the high level
data.ORC: Organic Carbon - The amount of carbon which is bonded to another carbon or hydrogen or both
data.OTE: Others Each - Identifies the maximum value of any single metallic element not listed in the chemical composition limits standard
data.OTT: Others Total - Identifies the total value of all metallic elements not listed in the chemical composition limits standard
data.OXI: Oxidizable Substance - Represents the amount of a substance that can undergo oxidation
data.OXS: Oxidizing Substance - A substance which removes electrons from other substances
data.PAR: Particle Size - The diameter of solid and liquid particles
data.PBD: Plug Back Total Depth - Well depth after plug back operations to abandon a lower producing horizon or formation
data.PDE: Casing/Liner Tubing Depth - Depth to the bottom of the casing/liner string
data.PDG: Pump Depth from Ground - The distance from the ground surface to the subsurface pump unit
data.PER: Magnetic Permeability - The ease with which a material can be magnetized and how much better it is as a path for magnetic fields than air
data.PFO: Perforation Feet Open - Linear distance of all perforations of the well casing string
data.PH: Pulse Setup Time - The interval immediately preceding the active transition of the timing or preceding the transition of the control input to its latching level
data.PHW: Hardwood Fiber - The amount of threadlike, primarily cellulosic material derived from the wood portion of hardwood trees
data.PI: Pulse Hold Time - The interval immediately following the active transition of the timing pulse or following the transition of control input to its latching level
data.PJ: Pulse Width - The time between the specified reference points on the leading and trailing edges of a pulse
data.PK: Pulse Recovery Time - The time between the reference point on the trailing edge of an asynchronous input control pulse and the reference point on the activating edge of a synchronous pulse input such that the device will respond to the synchronous input
data.PO: Percent of Order (-, +) - Expression of allowable variance of order expressed either as absolute (for example 92% to 110%) or relative percent (for example - 8% to + 10%)
data.POP: Pour Point - The lowest temperature at which an oil is observed to flow when cooled
data.PPS: Proprietary Shade - Identifies to customers when a textile company is using the customer's proprietary shade code versus the standard industry shade code
data.PRO: Processability - A rating of the ability to process
data.PSW: Softwood Fiber - The amount of threadlike, primarily cellulosic material derived from the wood of softwood trees
data.R10: Relative Fraction of Pure Long-Chain Cellulose - The ratio by weight of pure long-chain and degraded cellulose to pulp where cellulose molecules of various chain lengths occur
data.R18: Relative Fraction of Total Cellulose - The ratio by weight of total cellulose to pulp
data.REA: Reactivity - The rate at which a substance reacts or the amount of substance that reacts
data.RED: Reducing Substance - A substance which donates electrons to other substances
data.REF: Refining - The severity of mechanical processing stage expressed by the amount of energy applied and length of time product is retained within equipment
data.REI: Refractive Index - The ratio of the velocity of light in a vacuum to the velocity of light in the liquid
data.REL: Reflectance - The fraction of the total radiant flux incident upon a surface that is reflected and that varies according to the wavelength distribution of the incident variation
data.RES: Resistance - The property of a conductor causing electric energy to be transformed into heat; equal to the voltage across the conductor divided by the electrical current flowing in the conductor; measured in ohms
data.RUD: Usage Deviation (Applies to Kilowatt Hours, Kilowatt Demand and Reactive Demand)
data.S9: Site Atmospheric Pressure - Ambient pressure of the metering location
data.S10: Pulp Impurities - The percent hemicellulose polysaccharides and degraded cellulose in pulp fibers
data.S12: Start - Identifies a value measured at the start of a testing process or range of test results
data.S18: Hemicellulose - The percent hemicellulose polysaccharides in pulp fibers
data.SAP: Saponification Number - The number of milligrams of potassium hydroxide that is consumed by 1 gram of sample
data.SG: Slit Width - Width into which a customer wants a material slit (cut) length wise
data.SI: Supply Current - The current flowing into the VCC supply terminal of the circuit with specified input conditions and open outputs
data.SLD: Solderability - A measure of the ability of a material or component to be soldered
data.SLI: Slagging Index - The result of a procedure for obtaining information regarding the accumulation of ash deposits on radiant heat exchange surfaces in the furnace
data.SMB: SAM-B Rating - Measures cleanliness of steel for critical parts as to B-oxide volume in the steel
data.SMD: SAM-D Rating - Measures cleanliness of steel for critical parts as to D-oxide volume in the steel
data.SOD: Solids - The non-volatile material remaining after an analytical process
data.SOF: Softening Range - The temperature range in which material without a melting point goes from a rigid to a soft condition
data.SPR: Separator Pressure - Operating pressure of the oil/water/gas separating unit
data.STA: Stability - The property of a chemical compound which is not readily decomposed and does not react with other compounds
data.STP: Staple - Conventional method of measuring fiber length as pulled by hand
data.SUM: Suspended Matter - The mixture of fine, non-settling particles of a solid within a liquid or gas
data.SUT: Surface Tension - The force acting on the surface of a liquid which tends to minimize the area of the surface
data.SXX: S10 Minus S18 Value - The percent degraded cellulose in pulp fibers
data.T4: Single End Break - Break point of a single strand of yarn expressed in grams
data.T5: Skein Break - Break strength of yarn in skein form
data.T50: T50 - Temperature at which 50% of the volume of a mixture being distilled has been evaporated
data.T90: T90 - Temperature at which 90% of the volume of a mixture being distilled has been evaporated
data.TAS: Taste - The chemical sense by which flavors are perceived depending on taste, tactile, and warm and cold receptors in the mouth, as well as smell receptors in the nose
data.TDP: Perforation Top Depth - The depth from the ground surface to the top, or shallowest, portion of the well casing perforations
data.TEX: Texture - The property of a solid substance which is dependent on the size, form, order, and grouping of the smaller parts of which it is made and the way in which these parts are united
data.TOR: Torque - A force that produces rotation or torsion
data.TOX: Toxic Emissions Performance - Difference in exhaust toxic emissions attributed to a gasoline formulation as compared to the 1990 baseline gasoline
data.TPL: Tubing Pressure - Flowing - Fluid pressure within the inner tubing used to isolate different production streams from the surrounding well while production is flowing from the well; measured during well testing and completion operations
data.TPS: Tubing Pressure - Shutin - Fluid pressure within the casing, the outermost tubing used to isolate the well from the surrounding geology, with the well annulus closed; measured during well testing and completion operations
data.TRA: Trash Area - The number of pixels dotted by trash
data.TRC: Trash Count - Amount of trash in the court fiber
data.TRN: Transmittance - The fraction of the emitted light of a given wavelength which is not reflected or absorbed but passes through a substance
data.TUR: Turbidity - The extent of cloudiness in an item in which colloidally dispersed particles are present
data.TVD: Maximum True Vertical Depth - Total vertical distance from a surface location directly above the bottom hole location
data.UCB: Cube - The external cubic dimensions of a specified product
data.UNI: Uniformity - The degree of uniformity of fibers in a sample
data.UNK: Unknowns - Substances that are quantitated but of unknown identity
data.VIN: Vinyl - A chemical having the vinyl group CH2=CH-
data.VOC: VOC Emissions Performance - Difference in exhaust VOC (Volatile Organic Compounds) emissions attributed to a gasoline formulation as compared to the 1990 baseline gasoline
data.VOT: Volatiles - The gas or vapor material given off by an item under defined conditions
data.WDE: Water Depth - The depth of the water at an offshore location; measured from sea or lake bottom to the mean tidal level
data.WEL: Weight Loss - The amount of substance by weight that a material loses when subjected to specified conditions
data.WOD: Water-Oil Distribution Coefficient - A measure of the miscibility of oil and water
data.WPF: Wellhead Pressure-Flowing - The pressure as measured at the wellhead of a hydrocarbon well during a flow test
data.WPS: Wellhead Pressure Shutin - The pressure as measured at the wellhead of a hydrocarbon well during a shutin condition
data.WRA: Water Test Rate - The volume of water produced during a 24-hour test period
data.WSK: Width Shrinkage - The amount of shrinkage occurring per yard in the width of fabric expressed in percentage
data.XH: Side Height, Flat Bed With Removable Sides
data.YD: Yarn Count - The length per unit mass of yarn
data.ZA: Power Factor - Relationship between watts and volt - amperes necessary to supply electric load
data.ZBT: N-Butane - Relative concentration of N-Butane in the gas stream being measured
data.ZCD: Carbon Dioxide - Relative concentration of carbon dioxide in the gas stream being measured
data.ZD: Load Factor - Relationship between watt hours and watt demand necessary to supply electric load
data.ZET: Ethane - Relative concentration of ethane in the gas stream being measured
data.ZF: Sulfate Sulfur - An oxidation product present in sulfur
data.ZG: Organic Sulfur - The total sulfur less the percentage sums of sulfate sulfur and pyritic sulfur
data.ZHP: Heptane - Relative concentration of heptane in the gas stream being measured
data.ZHS: Hydrogen Sulfide - Relative concentration of hydrogen sulfide in the gas stream being measured
data.ZHX: Hexane - Relative concentration of hexane in the gas stream being measured
data.ZIB: I-Butane - Relative concentration of I-Butane in the gas stream being measured
